  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 29-year-old man is brought to the Emergency Department by ambulance after falling from a ladder. He complains of severe left thigh pain and inability to bear weight. Examination shows marked swelling and obvious deformity of the mid-thigh region. Distal pulses are faint but palpable, and the skin is warm. His vital signs are stable (see report).\nX-ray: Mid-shaft femur fracture with significant displacement\nWhich of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Obtain MRI for vascular injuries"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Schedule urgent surgical fixation without additional evaluation"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Initiate adequate analgesia and reassess distal vascular status"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Immobilize the fracture in a hip spica cast for definitive treatment"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>In acute trauma settings, <span data-sememe-id=\"0nYe7p\">CT angiography</span> is preferred for suspected vascular injuries due to its rapid acquisition and high <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ps0LDh&anker=Z252fcd07b99eb21a8bff067bee67fd9d\" data-learningcard-id=\"ps0LDh\" data-anker=\"Z252fcd07b99eb21a8bff067bee67fd9d\" data-section-id=\"EfW8Lk0\" data-sememe-id=\"wkXhJy\">sensitivity</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=pN0LXg&anker=Zefb6206a3f821bf7e5942b654dc6f6cf\" data-learningcard-id=\"pN0LXg\" data-anker=\"Zefb6206a3f821bf7e5942b654dc6f6cf\" data-sememe-id=\"8n0OEg\">MRI</a> is not routinely used for emergency vascular evaluation due to prolonged imaging times and limited availability. The patient's faint but palpable pulses and warm <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> suggest maintained <span data-sememe-id=\"Ef18LT0\">perfusion</span>, making <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=pN0LXg&anker=Zefb6206a3f821bf7e5942b654dc6f6cf\" data-learningcard-id=\"pN0LXg\" data-anker=\"Zefb6206a3f821bf7e5942b654dc6f6cf\" data-sememe-id=\"8n0OEg\">MRI</a> unnecessary.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>While early stabilization of a mid-shaft <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o300jf&anker=Za9d462f62c3712276640ac146b42f2ef\" data-learningcard-id=\"o300jf\" data-anker=\"Za9d462f62c3712276640ac146b42f2ef\">femur fracture</a> is necessary, faint <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zce232f978ea5a8fb9edbb980a41502b8\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zce232f978ea5a8fb9edbb980a41502b8\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">distal</a> pulses raise concern for possible vascular injury. Displaced <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-o0DeS&anker=Z066af70e4e57044668b99bc3a4013057\" data-learningcard-id=\"-o0DeS\" data-anker=\"Z066af70e4e57044668b99bc3a4013057\" data-section-id=\"upcprW0\">femur</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fractures</a> risk arterial <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ph0LUf&anker=Z89769da4ff0ee7f0552bfe73232d6078\" data-learningcard-id=\"ph0LUf\" data-anker=\"Z89769da4ff0ee7f0552bfe73232d6078\" data-section-id=\"cOcarc0\" data-sememe-id=\"WDaPW5\">contusion</a> or entrapment, necessitating vascular evaluation before orthopedic intervention. Proceeding directly to surgical fixation without vascular imaging risks missing an injury that could compromise limb <span data-sememe-id=\"Ef18LT0\">perfusion</span> and lead to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=VP0GdT&anker=Zbc05e544d46e794a60ac9ce9ec6883af\" data-learningcard-id=\"VP0GdT\" data-anker=\"Zbc05e544d46e794a60ac9ce9ec6883af\" data-section-id=\"k9cmne0\" data-sememe-id=\"WQ0PEf\">ischemic</a> complications.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>In a high-energy mid-shaft <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o300jf&anker=Za9d462f62c3712276640ac146b42f2ef\" data-learningcard-id=\"o300jf\" data-anker=\"Za9d462f62c3712276640ac146b42f2ef\">femur fracture</a>, severe <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> and muscle spasm can obscure vascular compromise. Providing effective <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Z937eb02dfdae5d3235cea8d72ffaf83f\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Z937eb02dfdae5d3235cea8d72ffaf83f\" data-section-id=\"5BXiY00\" data-sememe-id=\"CWbqns\">analgesia</a> improves patient comfort and allows for accurate reassessment of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zce232f978ea5a8fb9edbb980a41502b8\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zce232f978ea5a8fb9edbb980a41502b8\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">distal</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Zd786170682719d4fc3137e8a81a685c1\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Zd786170682719d4fc3137e8a81a685c1\" data-section-id=\"R4alQk\" data-sememe-id=\"QddupK0\">neurovascular status</a> before <span data-sememe-id=\"0Tde660\">fracture reduction</span>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Z04036123bf992e2ea414321b2a6f5cbd\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Z04036123bf992e2ea414321b2a6f5cbd\">Pain control</a> reduces muscle tension, aiding in the evaluation of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zce232f978ea5a8fb9edbb980a41502b8\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zce232f978ea5a8fb9edbb980a41502b8\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">distal</a> pulses and ensuring patient cooperation during further management. This step is crucial as subtle vascular injuries may become apparent once <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> is controlled, ensuring <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=yq0dah&anker=Z3d0d2d71043fc80f456d2bdddd0ea814\" data-learningcard-id=\"yq0dah\" data-anker=\"Z3d0d2d71043fc80f456d2bdddd0ea814\">patient safety</a> during subsequent interventions.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point: </b></span>Before reducing a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=o300jf&anker=Za9d462f62c3712276640ac146b42f2ef\" data-learningcard-id=\"o300jf\" data-anker=\"Za9d462f62c3712276640ac146b42f2ef\">femur fracture</a>, it is essential to provide <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Z937eb02dfdae5d3235cea8d72ffaf83f\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Z937eb02dfdae5d3235cea8d72ffaf83f\" data-section-id=\"5BXiY00\" data-sememe-id=\"CWbqns\">analgesia</a> for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Z04036123bf992e2ea414321b2a6f5cbd\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Z04036123bf992e2ea414321b2a6f5cbd\">pain management</a> and examine peripheral pulses to assess for potential vascular injury.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span data-sememe-id=\"FVbgws\">Hip spica</span> <span data-sememe-id=\"Efd8L60\">casting</span> is suitable for pediatric femoral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fractures</a> due to children's remodeling potential. In adults, especially with displaced femoral shaft <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fractures</a>, nonoperative <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z93de3e78c53617451068745e69433cd3\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z93de3e78c53617451068745e69433cd3\" data-section-id=\"gsWF850\" data-sememe-id=\"aTdQ660\">immobilization</a> is inadequate. Adults have less remodeling capacity, and the risk of complications like <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Zd81d375dc83885e4e30ea8c82281f2ca\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Zd81d375dc83885e4e30ea8c82281f2ca\" data-section-id=\"P4aWjk\" data-sememe-id=\"9EWNBM0\">malunion</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z1050091d8e3d071c50ec4d6254f01d35\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z1050091d8e3d071c50ec4d6254f01d35\" data-section-id=\"P4aWjk\" data-sememe-id=\"sYYtqn\">nonunion</a> is high. Stable <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vl0AAT&anker=Z422e03e13c76f394bca2bbede792688a\" data-learningcard-id=\"vl0AAT\" data-anker=\"Z422e03e13c76f394bca2bbede792688a\" data-section-id=\"_CX5uZ0\" data-sememe-id=\"uYYpIn\">internal fixation</a> is necessary for proper alignment and early mobilization in adults.</div>",
