    {
      "text": "A 28-year-old man presents to the ED after being ejected from his motorcycle during a collision. He reports severe left thigh pain. Physical examination shows a swollen, tense left thigh with obvious deformity and 3 cm of shortening. Distal pulses are present, and sensation is intact. Vital signs are BP, 88/65 mm Hg; P, 115; R, 22; T, 37.2°C (99.0°F); oxygen saturation, 98% on room air. He appears anxious and pale. After initial stabilization, which intervention should be prioritized before obtaining radiographs?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Intravenous morphine for pain control"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Immediate orthopedic surgical consultation"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Doppler ultrasound of distal vessels"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Assessment for fat embolism syndrome"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Application of skin traction and splinting"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 5,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>While <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Z937eb02dfdae5d3235cea8d72ffaf83f\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Z937eb02dfdae5d3235cea8d72ffaf83f\" data-section-id=\"5BXiY00\" data-sememe-id=\"CWbqns\">analgesia</a> is important for patient comfort, another step takes priority to prevent further <span data-sememe-id=\"T4c6ic0\">soft tissue</span> damage and bleeding from the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fracture</a> site.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Orthopedic consultation will be required for definitive surgical management. However, there is another immediate priority in the emergency department is to prevent further complications. </div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>Vascular assessment is important given the risk of vascular injury, but the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HJ0KvS&anker=Z5208bc2efbfd3c982ffbeacf78ebfcb3\" data-learningcard-id=\"HJ0KvS\" data-anker=\"Z5208bc2efbfd3c982ffbeacf78ebfcb3\">clinical examination</a> already shows present <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zce232f978ea5a8fb9edbb980a41502b8\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zce232f978ea5a8fb9edbb980a41502b8\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">distal</a> pulses and intact sensation, suggesting adequate <span data-sememe-id=\"Ef18LT0\">perfusion</span>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=sL0t_g&anker=Z24bad578b642e353c602ddafd1a93fed\" data-learningcard-id=\"sL0t_g\" data-anker=\"Z24bad578b642e353c602ddafd1a93fed\" data-section-id=\"eScxAb0\" data-sememe-id=\"GXbBzH\">Fat embolism syndrome</a> is a serious complication of femoral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fractures</a> that can cause <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tH0XHh&anker=Z33ef7cab5ec891b82794259be7e75d5d\" data-learningcard-id=\"tH0XHh\" data-anker=\"Z33ef7cab5ec891b82794259be7e75d5d\" data-section-id=\"Q-1uCj0\">respiratory distress</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7704Mh&anker=Z5c6e37230ac0687b2722ec65d3bb632a\" data-learningcard-id=\"7704Mh\" data-anker=\"Z5c6e37230ac0687b2722ec65d3bb632a\" data-section-id=\"Zy1Zdj0\" data-sememe-id=\"R81lmi0\">altered mental status</a>. However, this patient's current presentation is more consistent with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kO0msT&anker=Z815385d061174fc9042e51c7f8b23277\" data-learningcard-id=\"kO0msT\" data-anker=\"Z815385d061174fc9042e51c7f8b23277\" data-section-id=\"fkckMc0\" data-sememe-id=\"Nga-vP\">hypovolemic shock</a> from <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fracture</a> bleeding.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- Application of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z1d32c337522f0bca8f95a079c33fb2b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z1d32c337522f0bca8f95a079c33fb2b1\" data-section-id=\"gsWF850\" data-sememe-id=\"xjdEcJ0\">skin traction</a> and splinting is the most appropriate next step after initial stabilization. This patient shows signs of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kO0msT&anker=Z815385d061174fc9042e51c7f8b23277\" data-learningcard-id=\"kO0msT\" data-anker=\"Z815385d061174fc9042e51c7f8b23277\" data-section-id=\"fkckMc0\" data-sememe-id=\"Nga-vP\">hypovolemic shock</a> from bleeding at the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fracture</a> site, evidenced by <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rM0fJg&anker=Z3ae4e1e5581c7405590e65b57fa82021\" data-learningcard-id=\"rM0fJg\" data-anker=\"Z3ae4e1e5581c7405590e65b57fa82021\" data-section-id=\"KVcUvY0\" data-sememe-id=\"lNbvY8\">tachycardia</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=rM0fJg&anker=Zb5022b8fa3fa419ab039a0f8d70866a2\" data-learningcard-id=\"rM0fJg\" data-anker=\"Zb5022b8fa3fa419ab039a0f8d70866a2\" data-section-id=\"oVc0vY0\" data-sememe-id=\"nGb7-E\">hypotension</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kP0mUT&anker=Z6ed492871b68b31189bcb84adbfe1e96\" data-learningcard-id=\"kP0mUT\" data-anker=\"Z6ed492871b68b31189bcb84adbfe1e96\">anxiety</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Dl01_T&anker=Z1d32c337522f0bca8f95a079c33fb2b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"Dl01_T\" data-anker=\"Z1d32c337522f0bca8f95a079c33fb2b1\" data-section-id=\"gsWF850\" data-sememe-id=\"xjdEcJ0\">Traction</a> counteracts the opposing pull of thigh muscles on fractured bone segments, which decreases bleeding and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> from the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=T3063f&anker=Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\" data-learningcard-id=\"T3063f\" data-anker=\"Z614665fe523af7333fad58e1e2ab8f0f\">fracture</a> site and prevents further <span data-sememe-id=\"T4c6ic0\">soft tissue</span> damage.</div>",
